cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with optimization of machine learning models, specifically matrix factorization, through the use of self-similar arrangements of training examples. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR), as well as data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) which are relevant to the optimization techniques used. Additionally, the use of self-similar arrangements can be seen as a form of similarity-based learning (cs.SI).
